# Performance Guidelines

## Data Fetching
- Minimize client‑side data fetching; prefer server components.
- Use React `cache()` to deduplicate requests.
- Implement proper loading states with `loading.tsx` or `Suspense`.
- Paginate large lists.

## Images
- Use Next.js `Image` component with proper sizing and lazy loading.
- Serve images in modern formats (WebP, AVIF).

## Bundle Size
- Avoid large dependencies; if needed, use dynamic imports (`next/dynamic`).
- Split code by routes (Next.js does this automatically).

## Rendering
- Use static generation (`generateStaticParams`) where possible.
- Use Incremental Static Regeneration (ISR) for dynamic content that changes infrequently.
- For real‑time features, use Supabase Realtime sparingly and disconnect when not needed.

## Caching
- Leverage Next.js caching mechanisms (`fetch` cache, `unstable_cache`).
- Set appropriate `Cache-Control` headers in API routes.---
